{{version025}}
{{flavour|The Vestibule of Hell is guarded by Geryon, along with various denizens of each of the hells themselves.

Portals to the Vestibule of Hell are found abundantly in the Depths.

This branch contains the entrances to the Iron City of Dis, Gehenna, Cocytus and Tartarus.}}
{{flavour|Welcome to Hell! Please enjoy your stay.}}

[[File:Hell entry.png]] '''The Vestibule of Hell''' is the entrance to the four other branches of [[Hell]]. It is presided over by [[Geryon]], the gatekeeper of Hell.

==Useful Info==
You'll find multiple portals to the Vestibule in [[the Depths]]. Its most noteworthy inhabitant is [[Geryon]], a huge three-headed demon, but you'll also find flocks of demons and [[hell knight]]s. These monsters guard the entrances to the four main branches of Hell:

*[[File:Cocytus entry.png]] [[Cocytus]], the frozen hell.
*[[File:Dis entry.png]] [[The Iron City of Dis]], the metallic hell.
*[[File:Gehenna entry.png]] [[Gehenna]], the fiery hell.
*[[File:Tartarus entry.png]] [[Tartarus]], the deathly hell.

Each of these four branches contains a [[rune of Zot]].

==Strategy==
By the time your character is ready for [[the Depths]], chances are that they can clear the Vestibule, too. Even if you don't plan on doing the rest of the extended game, the [[horn of Geryon]] can be useful to [[Evocations]] specialists.

Geryon himself is not too difficult to kill. It is Geryon with the rest of the Vestibule that's difficult to kill.
*Most [[wall]]s within the Vestibule are made of rock. If you have a [[wand of digging]], you can make a [[killhole]] and fight most of the enemies there.

*Geryon himself will never follow you outside of hell. You ''can'' bring other monsters up. However, [[stair dancing]] can be dangerous; Geryon can summon [[hell beast]]s, which can [[trample]] you off stairs. Monsters with [[constriction]] attacks, such as [[tentacled monstrosities]] or [[anaconda]] [[skeleton (monster)|skeletons]], can prevent you from using the stairs too.

*A second unique monster, [[Murray]] the [[curse skull]], appears in 25% of games while exploring the Vestibule. He can rapidly reduce you to very low HP if you lack [[torment]] resistance, and summons hordes of undead to bury you with. Don't be afraid to use a [[scroll of blinking]] to get away from him the moment you see him, as he can be hard to run from for normal-speed characters.

